In this episode of the Major Issues Podcast, the hosts dive into Daredevil: Dark Art (2016), the chilling second arc of Charles Soule’s Daredevil run. When a twisted new villain named Muse starts leaving behind grotesque "art" made from his victims, Matt Murdock and his protégé Blindspot find themselves in a race against time to stop a psychopath who sees murder as his masterpiece. With striking visuals, high-stakes action, and a gripping moral dilemma, this arc puts Daredevil to the test like never before. Join us as we break down the story, the themes, and why Muse might be one of Daredevil’s creepiest foes yet!

